titleDescription:
Before joining Jus Laws, she worked in an international law firm advising clients. Over the past several years she has, represented a group of foreign investors engaged in the real estate and hotel business in South East Asia; she performed complex research and provided a legal opinion on a business proposal worth 1 billion baht condominium/hotel project located at Chonburi;

Represented the management of a golf course, drafting and revising their lease agreement and settlement;

Assisted an international investor in setting up the first private polygraph services in Thailand, and provided a full range of legal assistance in selling the polygraph machine to the Thai military (preparing bank guarantee for the negotiation and closing of the contract). She has also represented an international software development enterprise incorporated in Singapore with offices located worldwide, and handled all legal issues regarding its operations under Thai laws;

Represented an international software development enterprise incorporated in the United States of America with offices located worldwide ,and handled all legal issues regarding its operations under Thai Laws; · Obtained trademark for a beauty sector client, drafted and revised international distribution agreements, and appointed an exclusive, worldwide distributor for their product;

Advised and represented groups of foreign investors/buyers in cases with developers of the properties in Phuket and Phang Nga, and · Advised and represented a group of resort and spa operators in litigation and arbitration matters. Kunnika possesses a deep knowledge of civil and commercial legal issues and a complete understanding of international and Thai laws and regulations. Kunnika’s expertise in corporate, insurance, labor, family and real estate cases makes her a valuable asset to Juslaws, as well as to our Thai and international clients.

summary:
I'm a freelance writer, copywriter, and ghostwriter helping startups, SMEs, and brands reach their audiences through their website, blogs, social media platforms, and marketing materials.

I have experience in content strategy for companies and brands across industries, from travel, hospitality, photography, and design to law firms, real estate managers, and manufacturers.

I combine good technical SEO with content relevance and quality. Some of my skills:

• Writing for readers first, algorithms second;
• Building a blog audience with smart and unique content;
• Combining writing with tech across Web Content, Search Engine Optimization (SEO), Copywriting, 
• Creative Writing, Blogging, and Digital Marketing;
• Keyword research and monitoring tools to help brands find the most relevant and natural keywords for content;
• Ghostwriting fictional, non-fictional, and technical E-books.

Drop me a line and let's have a chat about your project.

titleDescription:
Mainly:
•devising and maintaining office systems, including data management and filing;
•arranging travel, visas and accommodation and, occasionally, travelling with the manager to take notes or dictation at meetings or to provide general assistance during presentations;
•screening phone calls, enquiries and requests, and handling them when appropriate;
•meeting and greeting visitors at all levels of seniority;
•organising and maintaining diaries and making appointments;
•dealing with incoming email, faxes and post, often corresponding on behalf of the manager;
•carrying out background research and presenting findings;
•producing documents, briefing papers, reports and presentations;
•organising and attending meetings and ensuring the manager is well prepared for meetings;
•liaising with clients, suppliers and other staff.

In addition to supporting managers, their team and departments include:
•carrying out specific projects and research;
•responsibility for accounts and budgets;
•taking on some of the manager's responsibilities and working more closely with management;
•deputising for the manager, making decisions and delegating work to others in the manager's absence;
•being involved in decision-making processes.
